.TH "count-@VERSION@" "1" "2002" "jd" "bozomake package"
.LO 1
.SH NAME
count \- numbers each line from stdin
.br
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B
count
.RI "[ -0 ]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B count
reads each lines from
.I stdin
and outputs them prepended with their numbering, starting from one
or zero according to the options.

The default is to start from one.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS
.B -0
starts the numbering from zero.
.SH FILES
none.
.SH SEE ALSO
.RB "(1)" "revtail" ","
.RB "(1)" "brev" ","
.RB "(1)" "countsort" ","
.RB "(1)" "percent" ","
.RB "(1)" "scramble" "."
.SH BUGS
.B count
isn't gnu compliant : lines longer than 4096 chars are cut and counted twice ...
There are probably plenty others. Please report them to
.B bozomake@disjunkt.com
.SH AUTHOR
Jean-Daniel Pauget (bozomake@disjunkt.com)
.SH MANPAGE VERSION
